description:
Here, we learn about early Adventism in England. Adventism would come to Britain fairly early, through William Ings, and then later through John Loughborough too. Southampton is now known as the birthplace of the Adventist Church, however, England has never experienced significant growth. It is a story of perseverance through trial and strong dedication, which also resonates with many other places around the world today.

To find out more information about early Adventism in England visit our website to read more in depth information.
